    "biography": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Grafvitnir, The Hunger Made Manifest — Stage 3</strong></p><p><em>Supernatural, Titanic • Level 8 Solo • Stamina 150 • Stability 8 • Free Strike 9 • EV 120</em></p><p>All form abandoned. Pure hunger and will and rage. Grafvitnir fills the great hall and the sky above it. The ceiling has broken apart. His attention has the specific quality of a thing that has been waiting for a thousand years and is finally certain it has run out of time.</p><p>Takes 2 turns per round. Has 3 Villain Actions (each once per encounter, max 1 per round).</p><p><strong>THE ROUND COUNTER:</strong> Grafvitnir must be <em>held</em> for 4 rounds. Each round, the Green Heart light grows brighter. The seal is closing. At the start of Round 4, the light goes white and Grafvitnir is dragged back into the earth regardless of his current Stamina.</p>",
      "director": "<p><strong>TACTICAL GUIDANCE — STAGE 3:</strong></p><p>Stage 3 is about the clock, not about winning through combat. The party cannot kill Grafvitnir. They must <em>survive him</em> until the seal closes on Round 4.</p><p><strong>Round 1:</strong> Green Heart blazing gold. VA1 (World-Ending Swipe) is the opener — overwhelming force against everyone.</p><p><strong>Round 2:</strong> Light brighter. Grafvitnir is screaming. VA2 (Despair Made Flesh) strips Hero Tokens from one target — psychological devastation.</p><p><strong>Round 3:</strong> Light intense. The cold is burning away. VA3 (Root Storm) — targeted destruction against three heroes.</p><p><strong>Round 4:</strong> The light goes white. Read the Sealing read-aloud. Grafvitnir is dragged back into the earth. <strong>The party wins regardless of his current Stamina.</strong></p><p><strong>Prison Madness:</strong> Cannot be Taunted, Frightened, or reasoned with. Negotiation attempts simply fail.</p><p>Damage to Grafvitnir matters strategically (End Effect trade-offs) but not for the victory condition. This is the emotional climax.</p>",
      "languages": []
    },
